      {
        "title": "Great memory but it has its limitation with 4 memory stick",
        "text": "This is a great memory but it wasn’t clockable to 6000mt/S when you have 4 memory stick installed . The only way to enable the XMP is only with 2 memories . I did have 2 pairs exactly the same KF560C36BWEAK2-64 . It will recognize the size of the memory to 128gb but you are limited to 3000 my/s vs 6000mt/s . You might as well stick to a pair if you don’t need that much memory . I barely use more than 24gb/s at any given point\n\nIt is possible it is due to my motherboard but it has been mentioned this is a limitation on most motherboard . Check the compatibility if you want 128 gb and are able to enable XMP",
